Your MIND and BODY are way to powerful to NOT make them a priority. Self care can easily be neglected, but we need it to thrive in every area of our lives, especially our finances.

TODAY, do at least one of these:

Don’t be so serious, laugh a lot. Take a 15-30 min nap. Meditate for 5 minutes. Run, walk, or jog around the block. Lift weights. (body weight included). Watch your favorite movie. Start reading that book. Start taking that course. Listen to a podcast. 

Take a long hot shower or bath. (With music and candles). Call a friend or family member to catch up. Write down your #1 financial goal, set yourself a recurring daily reminder to do something everyday that will push you closer to that goal. Summer clean your inner circle. No negative, toxic or fake energies allowed.

? Which one will you do today? ?

node.text:
Let’s talk about control.?
.?
I’ll admit to having an overabundant need for #control. ? Or maybe even, you could argue, the illusion of control. ?Having kids means letting go of some control, and learning that lesson starts before the baby or the child comes into your life! ??
.?
The pandemic, and so much associated with it, has tested the limits on what we can control and what we understand our control to be in the first place.?
.?
On the latest episode of #AboutIBDPodcast, I talk with child psychologist Dr Brad Jerson of Connecticut Children’s, and we dig into how as parents we can help our kids, and ourselves, with understanding control.?
.?
Things we can control during the school day:?
?Hand hygiene?
?Mask wearing?
?Keeping physical distance?
.?
When we are honest with #kids about the level of control that we all have during this time and how we can actively take charge of those things, it may help with making back to school a better experience for everyone.?
.?
Listen to my podcast in any podcast app, on my site at aboutIBD.com, or use the #linkinbio. Stay all the way to end for the fun outtake (not to mention the danceable theme music!).

node.text:
We all know that right now the airlines have fewer flights and some of their planes are grounded. Where are all of those planes? Parked somewhere obviously, which is tragic because a $200 million Boeing 767 isn’t making any money just sitting in the desert. 

On my way down to Texas I went through a place called Roswell, NM. Unbeknownst to me, the town is know for alien stuff because of a supposed 1947 U.F.O. landing nearby. Well. There’s also a huge International Air Center there which is used as a place to retire decommissioned airplanes. It’s also where the airlines currently have parked most of their beautiful jet liners that aren’t flying! 

There’s also a dragway right by the airport. I decided to put my GoPro on the hood of my TDI and gun it down the track. My old diesel Volkswagen is pretty slow but it was still fun.

node.text: After more than four months of lockdown for seniors, Texas began allowing family visitations to nursing homes and assisted living centers. This comes with restrictions, as these homes must go two weeks without any Corona infections of residents or staff. Additional regulations like weekly virus testing of staff will be expensive and hard to enforce. As of August 10, coronavirus deaths in nursing homes made up over 30% of the total Texas death toll, according to the Texas Tribune. On the outside, the threat is also all too real. In minority communities, especially, multigenerational families can put grandparents at risk, as their children and even grandchildren come home daily from jobs as essential workers, bringing the virus as an uninvited guest. Meanwhile, EMS workers continue to treat and transport seniors from their homes, as loved ones lean in for a last desperate embrace and, through tears, a final glimpse. #pandemic #gettyimages #gettyimagesnews

#This ?? Please take a moment and watch and learn about the facts surrounding the Spanish flu pandemic of 1918, that has been referenced often in comparison to the COVID-19 pandemic. ?? Unfortunately but not surprisingly, COVID-19 has become a partisan political debate, with demagoguery, talking heads, fierce tribalism and willful ignorance dominating much of the conversation, instead of it being lead by listening to health experts and the science. ?? Facts matter, science matters and leadership matters. ? #themoreyouknow #spanishflu #pandemic #covid19 #facts #leadership #science #healthcare #history ? @worldeconomicforum
"Something normal." This was me first time on a beach this year. And I did cry. Virtual hug.

I know I’m posting a lot of plant stuff lately but it’s summer and I can’t help it. I accidentally found myself in the vicinity of the lotus blossoms in NK yesterday. For the past 7 years or so I’ve stopped there with the boys on our way back from Casey farm camp, at least once a summer. I almost cried because I was getting to do something normal, but different this year because of Covid. There were only about 4 blossoms left, the rest had turned into either green or brown showerheads. I’m glad I got to see them and take this strange slow-mo of them blowing in the wind.
...

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'the second wave of the 1918 pandemic and the ANTI-MASK LEAGUE OF SAN FRANCISCO De @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'the 1918-1919 global pandemic, also known as the Spanish Flu, hit in three waves. DURING THE FIRST WAVE, 80% OF SAN FRANCISCO RESIDENTS REPORTED WEARING FACE MASKS, IN COMPLIANCE WITH THE CITY'S MASK MANDATE. SOURCE. NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'by November of 1918, the number of influenza cases began to drop, and city health officials started lifting restrictions. THIS CAUSED BUSINESSES TO RUSH TO RE-OPEN, LARGE PUBLIC GATHERINGS BEGAN TO RESUME, AND THE PUBLIC STARTED VENTURING OUT WITHOUT THEIR MASKS. SOURCE NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'DECEMBER OF 1918 BROUGHT A LARGE SPIKE IN CASES; this, coupled with the PUBLIC'S RESISTANCE TO ADHERE TO SOCIAL DISTANCING REQUIREMENTS, HELPED USHER IN THE SECOND WAVE OF THE pandemic. SOURCE WASHINGTON POST NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'January 1919- the second wave of the pandemic was in full swing, and tension was high in the city. this led to the creation of the ANTI-MASK LEAGUE OF SAN FRANCISCO. the Anti-Mask Mask League of 1919 was spearheaded by prominent business owners and local physicians. THEY HAD ONE GOAL; TO ABOLISH THE CITY'S MASK MANDATE. SOURCE WASHINGTON POST WASHINGTON NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'why the pushback? THE ANTI-MASK LEAGUE'S CHIEF COMPLAINT? mandating wearing a mask was an infringement upon THEIR CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. even after the upswing in fatalities during the second wave, many residents refused to wear a mask during the third wave, stating they would not be giving up their freedoms again for something that "served no purpose" in the first place. SOURCE WASHINGTON POST NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'WHY DOES IT MATTER NOW? one major critique of the mask mandate, and other social distancing requirements during the Spanish Flu, were that they DIDN'T WORK however, many historians attribute the continuation of the spread of the disease to the fact that these public health safety requirements were not adhered to LONG ENOUGH. SOURCE WASHINGTON POST NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: ‎1 person, ‎text that says '‎NPR journalist Tim Mak discusses the research on the effectiveness of the public health measures taken. he highlights ROBERT BURRO, professor of economics at Harvard University. in the interview, Mak points out how Burro's research did in fact show that "things like school closures, prohibition on public gatherings and quarantine did help flatten the curve." @ redi ?p Burro went on to argue that while these public safety measures did not significantly reduce the amount of deaths during the pandemic, it was because the public did not adhere to these requirements long enough. SOURCE WASHINGTON POST NPR.ORG @APAINTERSPOETRY‎'‎‎.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'what's the takeaway? PLEASE KEEP ADHERING TO TODAY'S SOCIAL DISTANCING GUIDELINES MANDATES. AND 6ft. San Francisco was doing great with their compliance in mask wearing social distancing during the first wave of the flu. it wasn't until local officials lifted restrictions & residents discarded their masks that cases began to rise again and many were quick to discredit the effectiveness of afore mentioned safety measures.'.

Photo by Diana Daniels on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'SOURCES INFORMATION Trent, Sydney. "Coronavirus Mask Confrontations Echo San Francisco's Anti-Mask League A Century Ago". The Washington Post, 2020 CHANG, AILSA, and TIM Mak. "NPR Choice Page". Npr.Org, 2/00352 : flu-pandemic. GRAPHICS- "Face Mask On Isolated White Background Clip Art". Clipart.Me, 2020, https://cipart.m/ico/ice-mak-.on isolated-white-background-49714. node.text:
The COVID 19 pandemic has compounded the challenges of families already facing the burden of an FTD diagnosis, which in turn can lead to an increased toll on healthcare providers. Studies have found a higher risk of burnout and Post Traumatic Stress Disorder among employees in the healthcare sector, and direct care workers, such as Certified Nursing Aides and nurses are especially vulnerable in this time.
 
You are making a difference in the lives of those living with FTD, and it’s important to know that you are not alone, and support is available. To that end, our most recent issue of Partners in FTD Care (available via the link in our profile) addresses the impact of the coronavirus outbreak on families and facility staff affected by FTD.

In his address to the nation last night, President Cyril Ramaphosa announced that South Africa will be moving to Level 2 of its national lockdown starting midnight on Monday, August 17th.

This means that most regulations put in place to help curb the spread of COVID-19 will be lifted.

Even with these changes, people are encouraged to exercise caution and continue taking steps to reduce the risk of spreading the virus - such as wearing a mask, washing hands regularly and keeping their distance from others.

Take a closer look at what’s changing under #level2lockdown and read Ramaphosa’s full speech.

Click the link in our bio.
.
.

node.text:
Most people don't get the point. 
.
Why do we even do it? 
.
⁣Why work so hard in the gym, pour so much time, energy and effort to train? Why does it even matter so much? What's so important about it?
.
⁣They usually categorize us to being Narcissistic, self-obsessed people who fall in love with their own reflection. Is it really the case though?
.
⁣Are we just feeding into our superiority complex and covering up our insecurities?
.
⁣Are we self-loathing in our own reflection and unable to accept ourselves the way we really are?
.
⁣Seems like they're all missing the point.
.
⁣Yes, we work hard and put boots to asses(pro-wrestling reference) when training. But not to feel like a ripped Tyrannosaurus desperate to hog more attention and cover our shortcomings.
.
Training gives us more than a better body. It gives us a better life.⁣
.
⁣It builds more than just muscle, endurance and stronger limbs. It builds a character.
.
⁣The daily struggle and stress under the bar teach us how to stop BSing ourselves. It teaches us ways to take action instead of making excuses to ourselves and finding reasons to fail, how to stop playing a victim and start acting on your problems instead.
.
The daily struggle has taught us ways to overcome challenges and get one step closer to our goals every day.
.
⁣There are no magic pills or easy fixes. You have to push through the pain and adversity. We become passionate about the Long Term Satisfaction rather than Immediate Gratification.
.
Being in the trenches for years , people like me realise that : 
.
The ability to change your body shows your ability to make a difference in your life.
.
This by no means is to disrespect people who are not passionate about lifting weights and improving their body composition. This probably will apply to any passionate individual who wishes to excel in his hobby/side hustle. Hope all of us reach that peak(and stay there).
.
And basically, That's why we train.
Key is to put in the work every single day.
.
Fitness will always be a reminder that there are no real "secrets" or "shortcuts" or "Magic Diet Plans" that suddenly can change one’s life. We all know they never work.
.
Probably that's why we train.

Protestors attend a demonstration in Berlin against the results of Belarus' presidential election the previous weekend, in which President Alexander Lukashenko, the only ruler the country has had, claimed victory and another term in his 26-year rule of the country. Preliminary results gave Lukashenko 80% of the vote, which opposition candidates allege is a rigged count. The main opposition to Lukashenko, Sviatlana Tsikhanouskaya, has fled to Lithuania, and the European Union has condemned both the election outcome as well as the government's violence against protesters participating in the demonstrations against Lukashenko's victory that followed.

node.text:
⁣⁣
Tak jarang sakit pinggang belakang menjadi penyebab utama terganggunya pekerjaan. Meski terbilang banyak dialami, kamu sebaiknya tetap waspada pada penyebab gangguan ini. Nyatanya, sakit pinggang bukan hanya disebabkan oleh salah postur.⁣
⁣
Fungsi punggung bagian bawah atau lumbar adalah untuk menompang tubuh, bergerak, dan melindungi jaringan. Karena itu, keluhan sakit pinggang bagian belakang yang muncul dengan intens akan membuatmu sulit beraktivitas.⁣
⁣
Namun penyebab nyeri pinggang yang paling sering antara lain :⁣
1. Sakit pinggang karena otot dan ligamen (jaringan penyokong)⁣
2. Sakit pinggang karena penonjolan dan robeknya bantalan tulang belakang⁣
3. Sakit pinggang karena radang sendi⁣
4. Sakit pinggang karena kelainan kelengkungan tulang belakang⁣
5. Sakit pinggang akibat osteoporosis⁣
6. Sakit pinggang akibat sepatu hak tinggi⁣
7. Sakit pinggang karena ginjal⁣
⁣⁣⁣

French designer Anne Sophie Cochevelou is on a mission to make face masks this year's must-have health AND fashion accessory.

She began the project in lockdown, adding colourful materials and unexpected objects (even Barbie dolls) into her designs to give them a unique feel. They proved so popular that Anne's now made around 200 - selling many online.

Her style? Raising spirits during a time when many people are "really struggling". "At least seeing someone dress up and have a colourful mask... might make [people] smile a bit". (? Anthony Lycett)

@sophiecochevelou @anthonylycettphotography

#Fashion #Facemasks #Pandemic #Covid19 #Coronavirus #BBCNews 
.

A estilista francesa Anne Sophie Cochevelou tem a misso de fazer mscaras faciais o acessrio indispensvel para a sade E a moda deste ano.

Ela comeou o projeto em bloqueio, adicionando materiais coloridos e objetos inesperados (at bonecas Barbie) em seus designs para dar-lhes uma sensao nica. Eles provaram ser to populares que Anne agora ganhava cerca de 200 - vendendo muitos online.

O estilo dela? Animar o nimo durante uma poca em que muitas pessoas esto "realmente lutando". “Pelo menos ver algum se vestir bem e com uma mscara colorida ... pode fazer [as pessoas] sorrirem um pouco”. (? Anthony Lycett)

node.text:
Well I managed to crawl out of bed, get changed and do my make-up before 12noon, that’s progress right ??.
.
I’ve been really struggling the last few days with a huge Fibro flare, by far the worst I’ve ever experienced, struggling to walk, concentrate, the pain is honestly horrible, i don’t even want to get up! 
.
At times it’s making me question my studies and future in nursing and how I’m going to cope with everything, but I’m a tough cookie and unless something dramatic happens I’m not gunna give up that easily, I just have to keep telling myself that. 
.
I’m going to speak to my GP tomorrow and see if I can get some different medication and make seek help from a rheumatologist and physio to help with the pain and movement in my legs/ankles, feet and hands particularly. 
.
.

node.text:
Presenting an easy guide to introduce to you the art of Heartfulness (@heartfulness) Meditation. Try meditating with Certified trainers through:

1. HeartSpots: https://heartspots.heartfulness.org/

A heartspot is your nearby place where Heartfulness meditation and rejuvenation practices are offered to the public free of charge by a certified trainer. Heartspots are found in most countries around the world and are open for training to all over legal age who have interest to learn the practices.
Link available on Heartspots highlights.

2. HeartsApp

Google Play Store: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.hfn.unified&hl=en_IN

App Store: https://apps.apple.com/us/app/heartsapp-by-heartfulness/id1438627629

HeartsApp by Heartfulness facilitates guided practices of Heartfulness tools; relaxation, rejuvenation, and meditation with the yogic transmission. It enables you to find inner self and connects with heart.
Link available in Heartsapp highlights.

3. Heartfulness Masterclass: https://heartfulness.org/en/masterclass 
Link available in Practice highlights.

Heartfulness Meditation is free of charge and available for everybody. Try it for yourself!

node.text:
It’s been months now and the doors to every worship place is closed and it feels like humanity is going the last phase of changes where some people are getting the message and some are going way too outward and they aren’t getting the light that is actually required to up come from the phases a particular pandemic puts in…..

.

.

Seeing that everything is undergoing a particular change including our personal lives many people around me are having personal growth and I’m so blessed to witness that changes in them….

.

.

I hope this pandemic or whatever this is goes away and may Allah open the doors of mosques and people can have their peace of mind once again and after all, May Allah make all of us believers in true essence not in the hyped way as its being portrayed all over the social media…...

.

.

I hope we all humans realise the reality of our existence and the meaning behind our lives not just we must be engrossed in the mediocre world and its delusional entertainment sector….Everything should be disciplined and should be regulated from time to time and phase to phase if something is overturned after the phase is passed then that thing is in the queue and should be removed as it may turn to be source of unnecessary interference in life and will cost you your time that is more valuable than money and of course it will cost you your sanity too….....

Peace be upon you all.....
.
.

node.text:
The United Nations (UN) Resident Humanitarian Coordinator in Nigeria, Edward Kallon, said $1.08b (N410.4b), is required to provide urgent humanitarian assistance to 7.8 million people in the Northeast.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The intervention requirements for funds were reached at an online high-level meeting held on Thursday, in Abuja.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Kallon, in a statement, yesterday, in Maiduguri, disclosed that the Coronavirus pandemic has exacerbated the humanitarian situation in Borno, Adamawa, and Yobe.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
He said the meeting was attended by Minister of Humanitarian Affairs, Hajiya Sadiya Farouq, Borno State Governor, Babagana Zulum, as well as other UN and NGO representatives.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
He solicited support for vulnerable people in the Northeast, as “the number of persons in need of life-saving aid had risen steeply.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
He said: “The number of people needing assistance is the highest ever recorded in five years of a joint humanitarian response.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“COVID-19 pandemic is affecting us all. Its devastating effects will distress Nigeria’s most fragile region.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“Unless we take immediate action, we should prepare for a spike in conflict, hunger, and destitution in Northeast Nigeria.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
To read on, click the link in our bio.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Photo Credit: Reuters ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Despite a pandemic, beauty is still very much a ‘touch and try” business involving experimenting with testers. With beauty and cosmetic testers expected to be a relic of the past, the industry is on it’s toes thinking of ways to allow more hygienic testing before buying. A company recently rolled out touchless testers that allow motion activated dispensers that can distribute any type of fragrance or liquid skincare product. While AR and VR have been existing mainly as marketing tools, not many fashion and beauty companies took them seriously before the pandemic hit. Will the new normal of beauty retail switch from ‘touch & try’ to trial & error? To read more, head to the link in bio.

Her texts are brilliant and we should read them several times not to forget the complexity of the situation we are in together. 
Andra Tic?r?u spent her lockdown time in Bucharest, Romania, where until today, August 16, 2020, 69, 374 cases of infections and 2,954 deaths have been confirmed since the outbreak of the Coronavirus pandemic.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: phone, text that says 'DOOMSCROLLING'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'some previous posts talked about how negative news is hampering mental health of people. and how negativity bias works. How Social Media is harming us right Turns Out that their is an actual term forit. It's called Doomscrolling! heard the word in an instagram post and went on to learn more about it. FunFact that it was coined before the pandemic but got popular after'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'With all of us in lockdown we have started using social media more. We are reading negative news a lotmore. There is an urge to know about how numbers are increasing, how coronavirus has impacted people etc. Covid 19 coupled with social unrest in various parts of the world has also lead to us reading anews a lot more. We feel the need to be more aware about what's happening around the world. But instead we our harming our mental health.'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'will tell you about myself. Before March, barely knew anything about American politics and election system. And now since past 5-6 months have been reading a lotmore through social media. The Black Lives Matter movement impacted me SO much and| kept reading about itat time. And not just that spent entire April reading Corona Virus data with little understanding. My level of despair knew no bounds. The uncertainty of the pandemic made the situation worse.'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: 1 person, text that says 'Now know that am not not the only one. Many people around the world are reading and scrolling through their feeds streading bad news. Sarah z @marysuewriter what's dangerous about doomscrolling is that repeated emphasis on the importance of staying informed can easily trick you into thinking that endlessly consuming bad news on autopilot is a progressive moral duty, when in actuality it's the digital equivalent of emotional self-harm'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '"Doomscrolling is "the act of endlessly scrolling down one's news apps, Twitter, and social media and reading bad news. The pandemic has exacerbated these habits in many ways, including the fact that there is no shortage of doomsday news," DR. ARIANE NYU People are drawn to doomscrolling because they feel like they have a sense of being able to control any of that bad news. Doomscrolling does not create control and only makes you miserable." DR. AMELIAALDAO'.
Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: one or more people and phone, text that says 'HERE'S SOME WAYS I GOT OVER DOOMSCROLLING'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '.Social Media Detox It's weird to say considering am saying this on a social media platform. But if you are feeling ow/depressed, it' better to delete those apps for a while. Sometimes you don't need to know what's going on in others' lives •Filter out the pages you are following used to follow a lot of politics and news in general. unfollowed all of them And instead followed a lotof lot pages on instagram based on positive news, positivity, mental health, some wholesome pages. follow news even now but don't let get in my head.'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says 'Being Mindful of what we share on Instagram When felt negative used to share a lot pessimistic posts on my Instagram stories. While sometimes it's not a bad thing as people around you become conscious of your situation, it makes you feel more negative. used to share string of posts about certain things in trend, generally negative. But then started becoming conscious of what share. Now usually try to share more positive stories or wholesome memes. Positivity is contagious. When you share positive things, positivity comes back to you as well.'.

Photo by Searching Positivity ? on August 16, 2020. Image may contain: text that says '.Invest your time in something positive or what makes you feel happy. This one of the biggest changes experienced in myself went off social media for a week and started Star Wars series. Each day used to watch one movie. In that way, got myself into routine. decided will invest myself in stories and art. knew that don't have the patience to read a bookso started watching movies mostly pop and geek culture. call it the movie a movie therapy. Since then have watched 30+ movies and TV shows and feel way more positive and energetic.'.

node.text:
I know that it isn't easy to get back to being in a positive shape in a pandemic. It requires a lot of effort and push mentally to feel like you are better. Things that worked for me might necessarily not work for you. Even though I feel a lot better, less uncertain, I find myself out of loop sometimes. 
But I hope that you try. I hope you feel better. The biggest thing I learnt is making my mental health a priority bc when I feel mentally healthy, I feel a lot more productive, confident and creative. There will be low moments but just keep in mind that there is a light at the end of the tunnel. There is. 

I have content coming up on other such issues as well. Stay Tuned. 

#doomscrolling #socialmedia #instagram #mentalhealth #pandemic #covid19 #happiness #positivity #searchingpositivity

node.text:
Jewelers in the traditionally lucrative Indian gold market are struggling—even while the metal’s value skyrockets—as coronavirus fears keep sales down, craftsmen at home and shops shuttered. 

Months after India lifted its strict lockdown, the country’s biggest gold market Zaveri Bazaar remains desolate, with most stores closed and no customers in sight.

“We have been running this shop for the last 40 years and I have never seen the business hit such lows,” said 75-year-old Madhubhai Shah, one of only a handful of jewelers who decided to reopen. 

The Mumbai market was hit hard by the March lockdown, which saw millions of migrant workers—including many gold craftsmen—flee India’s cities as their income dried up. – AFP

node.text:
Introducing Self Care Sundays! ?

This is a piece I wrote way back when lockdown started, but never posted because I didn’t know how people would respond. As anyone with any sort of experience with a mental health issue will tell you – people aren’t always the most open minded & willing to learn about the topic.

I’m posting it here, under Self Care Sundays, because self care is not just about cute sheet masks and bubble baths.

Much like your physical health, mental health is just another thing you need to monitor. When I mention this, people automatically assume that if you’re even thinking about your mental health at all, that it means you have a problem. NO. Simply being aware of your mental health is enough – don’t be a squid in ice (you’ll get that reference when you read the post lol).

When we started this blog, my personal goal was very clear – to normalize mental health and create a safe space to have a conversation around it. I’m hoping today’s little blog post helps the cause.

Likes & shares don’t matter to me for this post; I just sincerely hope that people read the actual blog and help spread the awareness. So if you’ve managed to read it, please leave a yellow heart in the comments – I just wanna know you get it

Mental health posts are going to become a regular part of Self Care Sundays so if you have anything you’d like to read about or share – let us know & we’ll try our best to gather some resources for you.

Sending everyone love and hugs,

XoXo, Aqeelah & TeamSkinStat

Hey {Raffi, great Insta, we'd like to organise a collab with you. Message our main account @salvatore.franco.brand and tell them we sent you!

“We are more often frightened than hurt; and we suffer more in imagination than in reality.” Seneca. 

I really do miss San Diego, but I should not expect any other outcome. COVID-19 has brought change into all of our lives. We should be grateful for a change, not wanting anything to be different. Love our fate, Amor Fati. The faster we embrace this concept, the better it shall be for our minds, for we shall be at ease. There are many missed opportunities, but the path has not ended, because we can easily create a new one. Let this be not a time of torment, but of personal growth. 

Most recently I have seen people develop into a state of irritability, there is needless suffering that can otherwise be avoided is one chooses to be. 

The global pandemic has caused people their determination, thus their purpose. This has allowed them to become restless. Be unlike those people, the famous Philosopher King: Marcus Aurelius once said: “The nearer a man comes to a calm mind, the closer he is to strength.” 
It is something that I have been practicing and trying to perfect to a T. Let us all do the same.

node.text:
I've spent my weekend playing with an idea I've had for a COVID case. 

I am The Bag Dag, after all.

So here's the first draft.  A smallish double-sided case. One side lined in waterproof fabric and with a red zip. It contains a net washing bag that is completely separate to the case.

The other side with several pockets. 

The idea is that sanitizer, wipes and clean masks live in the pocketed side.
The red zip signals caution because this side is for used masks. 

So, one would open the first side, apply sanitizer and then open the red side. The mask that was on would be doffed and placed in the net bag on the red side. It would be zipped up, then hands cleaned again before a clean mask would be taken out and donned.

At home, the red side would be emptied into the washing machine and wiped down with disinfectant- ready for the next day.

I think it would be very useful for those who use multiple cloth masks every day but find the whole COVID Cha-Cha a bit of a palaver!

What do my peeps think?

node.text:
Nuria Cifuentes, Intensive Care and Theatre Nurse

@nuriacifuentes 

I will never forget how hectic the unit was during COVID times. No matter how hard we worked, we had the feeling that we were not doing enough for our patients, which is an exhausting and awful feeling for any nurse.

You could see the anxiety in your colleague’s eyes - it was the same thing I was feeling at the time. Sharing that experience together gave us the strength to carry on.

We should feel proud of having been able to survive a pandemic’s wave. I hope we can survive another one.

node.text:
SEKOLAH TERBUKA⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Menurut data Satgas Covid-19, peningkatan kasus positif belakangan ini banyak didominasi kluster perkantoran, seiring dibukanya kembali aktivitas dunia usaha. Hal ini tidak mengherankan, mengingat hampir semua perkantoran memiliki sirkulasi udara tertutup dan ber-AC. Mengutip pakar epidemi, potensi penularan di ruang tertutup jauh lebih tinggi, apalagi jika tidak disiplin dalam menjalankan protokol kesehatan.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Belajar dari hal tersebut, rencana pembukaan sekolah di zona hijau dan kuning, seharusnya juga memperhatikan masalah penggunaan ruang kelas. Kelas harus memiliki sirkulasi udara yang lancar. Jendela-jendela harus dibuka, dan penggunaan AC harusnya tidak diperbolehkan. Kelas model saung terbuka, relatif lebih aman karena lebih bagus sirkulasi udaranya.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Tapi yang lebih aman lagi adalah jika kegiatan belajar dilakukan di tempat terbuka. Di taman, di bawah pohon, di kebun, dalam kelompok kecil dengan pengaturan jarak dan tetap pakai masker. Menurut ahli epidemologi Jepang, resiko rendah di tempat terbuka dipengaruhi faktor angin dan sinar matahari. Ruang terbuka mencegah virus menumpuk dalam konsentrasi banyak dan terhirup.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sebenarnya sudah ada referensi model 'sekolah terbuka' saat pandemi. Saat wabah  awal abad 20, banyak sekolah di Amerika dan Eropa yang diubah menjadi "open-air school". Saat pandemi sekarang, di Kashmir, India, kegiatan sekolah di tempat terbuka telah dijalankan. Sementara di beberapa kota di Indonesia, kegiatan untuk anak-anak di alam terbuka, diadakan secara terbatas dalam format 'green therapy' oleh komunitas sekolah alam. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Mengingat pandemi (mungkin) masih panjang, saya mengajak para pegiat pendidikan untuk terus mencari model dan metode yang lebih efektif untuk memenuhi hak anak; belajar dan bermain dalam kondisi aman dan sehat. Sampai saat ini Pembelajaran Jarak Jauh (PJJ) masih terus disempurnakan. Jika kondisi sudah memungkinkan, PJJ bisa dikombinasikan dengan 'sekolah terbuka'. Saya pikir, ini solusi yang lebih kreatif dan aman, daripada memasang kotak pelindung plastik di meja kelas yang ventilasinya tertutup dan ber-AC.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Salam sehat, AGY.⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Quarantine. Lots of people have landed in quarantine this morning from confirmed exposures.

Let's face it - Quarantine STINKS. You're stuck at home, sometimes confined to one room!

 Do you know someone in quarantine and want to cheer them up?

IsraelQuest games are a great activity - and a Group Game allows those in quarantine to have a virtual get-together with others! And they can easily be gifted to anyone! Just purchase access to the game, wait about a minute for an email to arrive with your game link, and then you can send the link on to anyone you want! 

It's really easy to show you care. Go ahead and send a game!

node.text:
MARGHERITA, LUCA, ANITA E EVA
.
Con Margherita siamo amici dai tempi delle scuole superiori e adesso viviamo abbastanza vicini. Con lei e Luca, il suo compagno, abbiamo continuato a vederci durante la fase 1 per scambiarci i pacchi del gruppo di acquisto solidale di cui facciamo parte. Lei ha da poco iniziato a lavorare in un ospedale di Firenze dove dice si trova bene e Luca fa l’insegnante  che in questo periodo vuol dire passare molto tempo davanti allo schermo di un computer. Anita e Eva hanno la fortuna di crescere in campagna e di avere un’amica della porta accanto. 
.
.
We have been friends with Margherita since high school and now we live close enough. With her and Luca, her partner, we continued to see each other during phase 1 to exchange the boxes of the  group for solidarity shopping to which we belong. She has just started working in a hospital in Florence where she say she is comfortable and Luca is a teacher who in this period means spending a lot of time in front of a computer screen. Anita and Eva are fortunate to grow up in the countryside and have a friend next door.
.
.

node.text:
Ken and Chip #101

_____________________________________

And you thought the series was over lol. We are back to the lives of Ken and Chip and what are we exploring today? Adapting to life during this goddamn pandemic.

They say dogs mimic the habits of their owners and my dog quickly realised that leading a introverted life is much much better than the alternative. 

The younger chip couldn’t wait to go out and explore the world.. the older chip just hated anyone disrupting his naps. Quite the character arc.

node.text:
Salah satu rahasia kesuksesan yaitu konsisten bertumbuh.
-
Jika Anda memiliki *konsistensi dalam bertumbuh* maka sudah pasti Anda selalu ingin menjadi lebih baik dari hari ke hari, waktu ke waktu.
-
Pernah liat kan betapa banyaknya orang yang gampang " TERHIPNOTIS " melihat temen - temen disekitarnya cerita bisa dapet uang puluhan juta dengan cara yang gampang?
-
Sebenarnya tidak semudah itu, hasil tersebut adalah buah dari konsistensi orang tersebut dari waktu ke waktu. Jangan anggap Anda bisa cepat sukses dengan cara menclak menclok dari satu bisnis ke bisnis lain.
-
Mungkin akan muncul pertanyaan dalam benak Anda "Gimana cara ngubahnya kalau kayak gitu?"
-
Ga bisa diubah kalau anda sendiri ga mau berubah. Karena semua perubahan adanya dalam diri, faktor luar hanyalah sebagai pemicu dan hal itu tidak akan bertahan lama jika tidak ada keinginan kuat dalam diri.
-
So,
Masih mau gagal fokus? Kalau anda ga bisa jadi yang terhebat, berusahalah untuk menjadi yang terbaik, kalau ga bisa jadi yang terbaik jadilah yang berbeda.
-
Kalau ga bisa jadi yang berbeda,  tolong fokus aja untuk membangun bisnis anda sendiri, dan semua akan indah pada waktunya.
-
Keep Fight! Pasti Kita Bisa!
Pasti Crown
